* Shadow Cat and Snow tech stood where they where, aware that their 
commander and friend was under a great deal of stress.
they hoped that she wouldn't give up, even though it was an easier way out.
Shadow Cat was perplexed though, by why the maximal didn't listen to Iron's 
orders. this was a delicate time of war and this, this... fool, was bungling 
it up. And for what? Didn't he hear their leaders transmitions?
Snow Tech was still waiting for Iron To awnser his silly greeting. He stood 
there and looked at her with big, kitten eyes and waited. meanwhile, Shadow 
Cat was busy with her small, hand-held computer, making some estimations and 
calculations on her and Snow Tech's pursuers. She also wondered what had 
happened to their littlest companion. It was vital he was not lost, he 
played an important role in the survival of a certain race of 
robotic/organic species, and to loose him would be loosing the entire race. 
And their hard work would be for nothing.....*

* The small cat inside Iron Raptors compartment was still awake and still 
wanting out. The motions that had knocked the little bot side to side had 
stopped, but his inprisonment had not. He mewed as loud and pitiously as 
possible, trying to get someones attention to let him out.*

" Mmmmmmmeeeeeeeeeeeeeeeewwwwwwwwwwwwww! Meeeeeeeerrrrrooooooowwww!"
